  "instructions": [
    "Prepare the Japanese short-grain rice according to the package instructions and set aside.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together mirin, sesame oil, sushi vinegar, and dried wakame seaweed.",
    "In a small saucepan, heat the mixture over low heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add the tinned crushed tomatoes and bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and let it simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "While the sauce is simmering, prepare the smoked salmon fillet by cutting it into thin slices and setting it aside.",
    "Once the sauce is ready, add the cooked Japanese short-grain rice to the saucepan and stir to combine.",
    "Add the sliced smoked salmon to the rice and stir gently to distribute evenly.",
    "Transfer the rice mixture to a serving dish and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to combine and chill.",
    "Just before serving, sprinkle the sesame seeds and black sesame seeds on top of the rice mixture and garnish with chopped scallions, pickled ginger, and nori sheets.",
    "Serve the smoky cold Japanese rice takikomi-gohan chilled, garnished with additional sesame seeds and pickled ginger if desired.",
    "To prepare the kombu dashi, combine the kombu and 2 cups of water in a saucepan and bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Strain the kombu and discard the solids, then whisk in the miso paste and set aside to cool.",
    "To assemble the dish, place a scoop of the chilled rice mixture on a plate, then drizzle with the kombu dashi and sprinkle with furikake, grated daikon, and yuzu juice, followed by the pickled ginger, nori sheets, and sesame seeds, and finally topped with a slice of pickled ginger and a sprinkle of sesame seeds and furikake."
  ],
